description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This Vacancy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our geriatric and acute stroke medical wards care for patients across 3 sites of the city, Northern General Hospital, Royal Hallamshire Hospital and SPARC@BeechHill. You can chose to specialise in dementia care; caring for older people with Parkinson’s disease; caring for older people specialising in shorter length of stay, caring for older people as part of the integrated nursing and therapy team, and caring for patients on the acute stroke pathway, following their journey through to rehabilitation and home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a diverse Care Group covering acute and community services. We offer both permanent ward posts and bespoke rotational posts, covering our specialised geriatric medical wards, Sheffield Frailty Unit and acute stroke and rehabilitation pathway, from admission to discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer an individualised induction and support package, supported by clinical educators. We offer a 3 day foundation stroke programme and specialist competencies, with the opportunity to undertake a stroke module at degree/masters level at Sheffield University.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very supportive of flexible working practices, and have a personal interest in your health and well-being.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced nurse looking for a new challenge?  Do you want to be involved in complex discharge planning? Are you interested in developing your nursing skills in geriatric and stroke medicine?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;****************************************************************************&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For those who are currently employed by the Trust as a Staff Nurse, you should instead apply through the Staff Nurse Transfer process via your line manager.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are a Newly Qualified applicant and are due to qualify before end of December 2020, you can apply via this advert. Please specify what month and year you are due to qualify. Please also specify the hours and list the three wards/areas you would prefer to work within.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you are due to qualify from January to July 2021, please apply on our specific Newly Qualified Nurse advert which will be live later this year.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;****************************************************************************&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
